sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1913029
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Synthetic plac-FixK2 hybrid promoter +RBS with mRFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Synthetic plac-FixK2 hybrid promoter composite part includes mRFP reporter (BBa_E1010). After co-transformation with light sensor BBa_K1913033, mRFP fluorescence could be detected after 12h culture.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tianhe Wang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Genomic sequence of Bradyrhizobium japonicum, iGEM part registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In order to test synthetic plac-FixK2 hybrid promoter,we put reporter mRFP under this promoter and co-transformed with light sensor BBa_K1913034. And mRFP fluorescence value was tested so that the intensity of transcription of this promoter could be quantified.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1913022
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Synthetic plac-FixK2 hybrid promoter with RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Synthetic plac-FixK2 hybrid promoter is the promoter that could not only be activated by light sensorsYF1-FixJ composite and but inhibited by LacI repressor. The sequence of upper control element is from wild type FixK2 hybrid promoter on genomic sequence of Bradyrhizobium japonicum, which contains two typical FixJ boxes. And core element region is replaced by constitutive promoter BBa_J23106. Addition lac operators on the both side of promoter as second control element that results in transcription repression.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tianhe Wang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: according to some previous iGEM projects (UNITN-Trento 2013, INSA-Toulouse 2013), the transcription activity of the wild type Fixk2 promoter is so weak that they all added an inverter part to control their target gene expression. Even the original pDusk system in darkness has only 5 times expression levels than in light conditions. Therefore, we decided to enhance the transcriptional activity of the Fixk2 promoter by changing the core element region of the wild type Fixk2 by a strong constitutive promoter (BBa_J23106) from iGEM part registry and by adding two typical FixJ boxes into the -40 to -70 region.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: **highly** engineered mutant of red fluorescent protein from Discosoma striata (coral)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
